featured_reviews.review_id:
Muslim population in Kolhapur city is found in two parts since before the Sansthan period.  It consists of two parts namely Bara Eemas and Akbar Mohalla.

Among these is the part inside the gate of Bindu Chowk.  The area between East Rajaram High School and Bindu Chowk Subjail falls in this.  The southern part of the road from Karveer Nagar Mandar to Binduchowk Weiss to Bargopal Talim is a Muslim population.

This community tends to be mainly involved in small business, sales.

However, this area remains underdeveloped.  Due to very dense population, lack of open roads, very small narrow roads and vehicular traffic, one does not usually walk around the area unless one is familiar with it.

This area is backward in terms of health due to the high number of goats, goats and chickens.
